{'name': 'Night Lizard Brewing Company', 'address': '607 State St', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Food, Breweries, Beer Gardens, Mediterranean, Nightlife, Restaurants', 'hours': {'Monday': '12:0-19:0', 'Tuesday': '14:0-21:0', 'Wednesday': '15:0-22:0', 'Thursday': '15:0-0:0', 'Friday': '12:0-0:0', 'Saturday': '12:0-0:0', 'Sunday': '10:0-20:0'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': True, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': None, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': 'free', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': None, 'Music': True, 'Ambience': None}, 'business_stars': 4.5, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2022-01-16 22:31:18', 'review_text': 'The only hazy on the strip! Much lower key and chill than the other breweries, but still has a couple of tvs to watch the game while listening to some Reggae!'}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2022-01-16 19:55:20', 'review_text': "A fire pit, live music, delicious beer, and sales that support an eco-friendly, sustainable cause? Fantastic! This was the line on loop in my head a few nights ago at Night Lizard. After several visits to this State Street brewery, I can easily say it's one of my tops. Staff are friendly, beers are tasty, and the vibe--whether sitting indoors or out--is neat. Gotta love all those hanging plants. 

Among beers tried are the Gnatcatcher IPA, Tiger Salamander Saison, and Monkeyflower Double White Ale. All are solid brews. I have yet to sample the food menu from Yona Redz, but look forward to it. 

There's usually room to sit on the outdoor patio, a Covid-safer option that offers great people-watching. I love holding a tulip glass of a tasty beverage, seeing folks passing by and eying the place. Thinking at them 'yes, you do want to stop here!' I smile a bit when someone does."}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2022-01-01 00:48:08', 'review_text': 'Trivia night is soooo cool. Best kombucha and seltzer. They say the beers are good too!'}]}

{'name': 'Itsuki Restaurant', 'address': '4020 Calle Real', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Japanese, Restaurants', 'hours': {'Monday': '17:30-21:30', 'Tuesday': '17:30-21:30', 'Wednesday': '17:30-21:30', 'Thursday': '17:30-21:30', 'Friday': '17:30-21:30', 'Saturday': '17:30-21:30'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': True, 'OutdoorSeating': False, 'WiFi': 'no', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}}, 'business_stars': 4.0, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 2.0, 'review_date': '2015-05-25 20:54:35', 'review_text': "Absolutely disappointing. As a matter of fact, this experience was so disappointing it caused me to take time out of my very busy life to write my first review ever. 

I'm someone who is happy when there is quantity. So I spend $60 here thinking that should do a good job filling me up (I order the 25$ sashimi bowl and 2 rolls) and I did not get filled up. The sashimi itself disappointed me as well due to the low quantity of cuts compared to kyoto's 25$ bowl. In addition, the fish itself I thought was less fresh. The 2 rolls were also small in comparison to Kyoto's. I'm never coming here again. Man I could have gotten 10 chipotle burrito's with those $60...."}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2013-04-23 19:18:42', 'review_text': 'This is the best sushi in Santa Barbara, aside from maybe Arigato, which is absolutely not worth the money. Go, go, go!'}, {'review_stars': 3.0, 'review_date': '2013-01-09 23:59:06', 'review_text': "The restaurant has located to the Camino Real Marketplace area (actually, more like near Pacific Oaks) in Goleta, where Baja Fresh used to be. The ambiance is *totally* different. It's become a big business. They're still getting the hang of how to serve so many people, and seem always to be apologizing for slow service, when it's actually about the same as other places. 

The food was not great the first few times I went, but the last time...yum...they were back on their game. It's worth a try!"}]}

{'name': 'Casa Blanca Restaurant', 'address': '330 State St', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Mexican, Restaurants, Seafood', 'hours': {'Monday': '16:0-22:0', 'Tuesday': '16:0-22:0', 'Wednesday': '16:0-22:0', 'Thursday': '16:0-22:0', 'Friday': '16:0-0:0', 'Saturday': '10:0-0:0', 'Sunday': '10:0-22:0'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': True, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': 'free', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': True, 'casual': True}}, 'business_stars': 3.5, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 4.0, 'review_date': '2020-03-11 05:59:08', 'review_text': "My friend and I came here for lunch on Saturday. I am not sure how it is at dinner, but for lunch there was no line so it was fast to get a table. The waiter was very thorough and accommodating. Both my friend and I had the blood orange margarita, which was so good because it had a jalapeño kick! But, don't worry it's not too spicy for anyone that is sensitive to spice, it was just right. 

We both ended up going with the combination plate; me the taco and enchilada and her the taco and tamale. To be honest the only reason why I didn't go with the mahi mahi taco was because it was singular (taco) versus the other tacos were plural in the name (tacos) and so I was expecting to get at least two tacos in the combo. However, only one came so I would ask that the menu be more clear. But, the food was delicious and we even had enough for leftovers. Both plates came with rice and beans too. 

There is an axxess deal for BOGO entree for lunch or dinner as well. So with all the food and drinks we had my friend and I were able to split it evenly for about $24 per person, which I think is a great deal for such a quality food."}, {'review_stars': 4.0, 'review_date': '2020-03-08 15:09:08', 'review_text': "Delicious food and drinks! Really fast service. Nice location with a nice scenic patio. They have heaters so you don't have to worry about getting cold. I ordered the burrito and my husband got the fajitas, both were delicious! I also got the margarita flight, which I highly recommend. If you're close to Amtrak on state, I would recommend stopping by!"}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2020-03-01 05:02:35', 'review_text': 'Ate at the bar tonight for my friends birthday. The bartender Dan, (tall, light and handsome) was attentive and took great care of us! Fast drinks with a warm welcoming personality, a great guy. Good food too! my Bf and I had the tacos.. simple but tasty! Thank you!'}]}

{'name': 'Minnow Cafe', 'address': '9 Breakwater', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Restaurants, Delis', 'hours': None, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': False, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': 'no', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': False, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}}, 'business_stars': 4.0, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 4.0, 'review_date': '2011-08-11 16:25:16', 'review_text': 'This place is perfect to get some seafood in Santa Barbara! I was glad to be able to find this hole in a wall while walking with my group for lunch. 

I ordered the clam chowder bread bowl and fish and chips. Clam chowder was very delicious and fresh. The fish was crispy and made into perfection. 

The best part is that you can order the food right away and simply sit at the tables outside to eat near the harbor where the ocean is so close. So if you want to get food in a quickly manner in order to have more time to explore the other areas in Santa Barbara, I would highly recommend Minnow Cafe.'}, {'review_stars': 4.0, 'review_date': '2011-04-08 00:39:53', 'review_text': 'Hard to beat for a fast-food-type breakfast or lunch at the marina. Simple, good food, well prepared.'}, {'review_stars': 3.0, 'review_date': '2011-03-20 03:51:33', 'review_text': "I really like the Minnow...I mean you can't beat the location for a fast food establishment and the Fish Tacos are pretty good...BUT I'm always horrified to discover how much this fast food experience costs.  I mean, it's really not very good food unless you view it as cheap (but it's not).  Great thing, sitting outside by the harbor watching the BPs go by while you eat cheap (seeming) food.  Bad part, greasy spoon food served on paper plates by snarky staff with condiments that blow away...but it ain't cheap.  Guess that's Santa Barbara."}]}

{'name': 'California Wood-Fired Catering', 'address': '', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Food Trucks, Event Planning & Services, Pizza, Restaurants, Caterers, Food', 'hours': None, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': None, 'RestaurantsReservations': False, 'OutdoorSeating': None, 'WiFi': None, 'RestaurantsTakeOut': False, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}}, 'business_stars': 4.5, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2015-05-24 00:32:27', 'review_text': 'We had them provide pizza for about 100 folks at Municipal Wine. Food was great -- salad, pizza, and gelato. All great. 

They warned us that it would be hard to get pizzas out for that large a crowd, and they were right. But they did the best they could in the situation and everyone was happy. Their chefs worked hard to please and did a great job. 

Only negatives were: underestimated salad, so we ran out a little early. And Email response was a little slow. That said, a pleasure to work with and tasty food!'}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2013-07-25 22:35:25', 'review_text': 'California Wood-Fired Catering is delicious and perfect for a casual, fun event! I have had the pleasure of working with them many times for events at the private event venue that I manage. While I have heard from a few clients that the owner can be sometimes difficult to get a hold of, I myself have never had a problem reaching him by calling the number listed on their website. Either way they always come through with the events that they book and the guests always rave about how fun it is having a wood-fired burning oven popping out fresh pizzas as well as how delicious the food is.'}, {'review_stars': 3.0, 'review_date': '2013-07-06 04:21:37', 'review_text': 'This year for 4th of July we checked out the Stow House old fashioned 4th of July:) What a pleasant surprise. We were lucky enough to stumble on these pizza people who were making pizza in special oven:) it was really good and hope they can come to our school carnivals next year:)'}]}

{'name': 'Campus Point Coffee', 'address': '6560 Pardall Rd', 'city': 'Goleta', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Food, Cafes, Coffee & Tea, Bakeries, Restaurants', 'hours': None, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': None, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': 'free', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': None, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': None, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': None}, 'business_stars': 4.5, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2020-01-10 17:12:03', 'review_text': "A friend got me interested in this coffee shop when she mentioned they sell vegan cookies. I'm vegan, and it's actually rather tough to find vegan sweet snacks in IV, so I was excited to try Campus Point. Funnily enough, when I headed over for a studying session, they were sold out! Guess those cookies must be good. 

However, the coconut charcoal mocha I tried was delicious--and vegan! Staff were super friendly, and I appreciated the indoor and outdoor seating options. Also, there's a toilet, which is a bonus, and the empanadas looked really yummy. I'll have to try one next time I visit."}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2020-01-08 22:10:42', 'review_text': 'Finally a place in Isla Vista with a bathroom!

Beyond the much needed bathroom this cafe offers a plethora of interesting drinks on top of providing all the basics. I got an iced charcoal mocha that was perfect to get rid of my mid afternoon slump.'}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2020-01-08 06:06:23', 'review_text': "This is such a cute lil coffee shop in the heart of IV. There's tables inside and outside to do work or chill, and sometimes there's an open mic outside. Prices are average for your local non-corporate coffee shop. The menu has a wide variety of drinks, and sometimes they post about BOGO's or 50% off on their instagram page. I'd definitely recommend this place to anyone who loves coffee and needs a place to study!"}]}

