{'name': 'El Taco Tequila Taqueria', 'address': '14 E Cota St', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Restaurants, Mexican', 'hours': None, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': False, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': 'no', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': True, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}}, 'business_stars': 3.5, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 2.0, 'review_date': '2013-12-06 03:03:14', 'review_text': "On Thursday night I went to this place after a concert. A few friends and I wanted a bite and a drink. We ordered with a young woman who quickly told us they did not accommodate gluten free customers, even if you wanted a taco or tostada without the bread. Fine. I'll work around that I understand. We waited 20 minutes for our food, granted there was only one guy in the kitchen. We finally got our tacos and were missing one chicken taco and our guacamole. We ask the chef for the rest of our order and he says they are closing the kitchen. I go to the woman and tell her that we didn't get all our food and she tells me I'm lying. I point to the plates on our table to show her we didn't. I ask for our money back and she declines. We end up getting into a fight about one chicken taco and guac. 

I have worked in restaurants before and I would never scold a customer over a $3 taco. I even offed to pay for it and she wouldn't let me. Really terrible customer service. The chef did make us some guac bc I think he felt bad that we were hungry and upset. By that point we had eaten what we were served and didn't have anything to put it on.

That being said the food we get was yummy. Too bad our experience ended on such a bad note."}, {'review_stars': 1.0, 'review_date': '2013-03-28 15:50:04', 'review_text': "We both got food poisoning here - that lasted a whole day. We narrowed it down to either the chips & salsa, the queso app, or the carnitas tacos since that's the only thing BOTH of us ate. The food seemed great, but it seems to be all about pushing the drinks for $$ and food safety was left to the sidelines."}, {'review_stars': 4.0, 'review_date': '2012-11-03 03:56:19', 'review_text': 'Great food. WOnderful atmosphere. Great Happy hour two for one Margaritas. I love the decor too. Beautiful Bar. Amazing flan!'}]}

{'name': 'Brasil Arts Cafe', 'address': '1230 State St, Ste C', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Juice Bars & Smoothies, Breakfast & Brunch, Brazilian, Restaurants, Food, Salad, Acai Bowls', 'hours': {'Monday': '17:0-20:30', 'Thursday': '17:0-20:30', 'Friday': '17:0-20:30', 'Saturday': '10:0-21:0', 'Sunday': '10:0-16:0'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': True, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': 'free', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': True, 'casual': True}}, 'business_stars': 4.0, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2021-12-21 06:50:22', 'review_text': "Our hosts Roberta and Mestre Daniel Yoshimi (aka Prof. Chin) provided an excellent menu of the favorite foods of Brazil (o Brasil, em português). One who appreciates tasty-good food simply cannot stay away very long. My tri tip was delicious, and the multiple traditional sides were exactly on-point. (Prices are friendly too.)

I used to visit this establishment weekly to take part in great African drumming classes, and it's fun to revisit the festive atmosphere and food. They present their cuisine and culture with hospitality, nuance and great cooking skills.

#HighlyRecommended"}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2021-12-18 05:28:16', 'review_text': 'my boyfriend and I went here for dinner and it was a nice experience :) we each got a caipirinha to drink which was good and my boyfriend LOVED the stroganoff! My Brazilian cesar was good and the brigadiero which we got to go was AMAZING! I would go back to try more! The lady told us to make ourselves at home which was a sweet sentiment!! The people were very nice :,)'}, {'review_stars': 4.0, 'review_date': '2021-12-15 12:06:28', 'review_text': 'The restaurant facility itself may not look all that elegant and appealing but the service and the food really blows that away. They serve food for each meal of the day but I personally would recommend going for breakfast and trying one of their acai fruit bowls. Slightly on the pricier side but so worth it and you will be healthily full for hours to come! The culture here is also something that is unique and interesting. Great place for family brunch!'}]}

